Project-private libraries
=========================

This directory holds vendored third-party libraries that are compiled into the
firmware/simulator. PlatformIO's Library Dependency Finder auto-discovers any
sub-directory here whose headers are #included from src/, so no entry in
`platformio.ini` `lib_deps` is required for these.

See https://docs.platformio.org/page/librarymanager/ldf.html for LDF rules.


Vendored libraries
------------------

Each library below was copied from its upstream source. The upstream license
text is kept inside the library's own folder; do not delete or rewrite those
files. When updating a vendored library, refresh both the source and the
LICENSE/COPYING files from upstream, and bump the version recorded here.

The parent project is licensed GPLv3 (see ../../LICENSE). All licenses below
were checked to be compatible with GPLv3.

1. Embedded Template Library (ETL)
   - Upstream:    https://github.com/ETLCPP/etl
   - Version:     20.47.1 (see library.json)
   - License:     MIT (LICENSE)
   - Used by:     PlatformIO Arduino builds and the desktop CMake build
   - Notes:       Replaces the previous `etlcpp/Embedded Template Library`
                  PlatformIO managed dependency. PIO's LDF auto-discovers it
                  via the library.json `includeDir = include` directive.

2. Eigen
   - Upstream:    https://gitlab.com/libeigen/eigen
   - License:     MPL2 primary, with some files under BSD-3-Clause and
                  LGPL-2.1-or-later (see COPYING.README inside Eigen/).
                  Define EIGEN_MPL2_ONLY at compile time to exclude any
                  non-MPL2 / non-permissive code.
   - Used by:     The desktop CMake build only (../../CMakeLists.txt adds
                  `lib/` to its include path). The Arduino PlatformIO builds
                  use the `hideakitai/ArduinoEigen` wrapper managed via
                  `platformio.ini` instead, and the `[arduino_common]`
                  section sets `lib_ignore = Eigen` so PIO's LDF does not
                  pick this folder up.

3. Quaternion
   - Upstream:    https://github.com/carrino/Quaternion
   - License:     MIT (LICENSE)
   - Used by:     Desktop CMake build (Quaternion.cpp is added directly to
                  the desktop sources). Available to PIO builds too via LDF
                  if any source #includes it.